"title": "8032: trust, lack of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8032: trust, lack of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Forsaking God and relying on other objects of dependence. This is futile and it provokes God's anger. Failure to trust others may be the result of a betrayal of trust in the past.</p>\n<h2>Failure to trust God</h2>\n<h3>The nature of failure to trust God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:13\">JER 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:16\">DEU 31:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:6\">ISA 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:11\">ISA 65:11</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of failure to trust God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:32-Deut1:33\">DEU 1:32–1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:23\">DEU 9:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:21-Ps78:22\">PSA 78:21–78:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:12\">NUM 20:12</a> <em>Moses and Aaron</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:4\">1KI 11:4</a> <em>Solomon</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:7\">2CH 16:7</a> <em>Asa</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:17\">REV 3:17</a> <em>the church at Laodicea</em></p>\n<h3>The consequences of failure to trust God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:38-Heb10:39\">HEB 10:38–10:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:4\">HAB 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:14-Lev26:20\">LEV 26:14–26:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:24-Jer13:25\">JER 13:24–13:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:25\">JER 46:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:13-Hos10:14\">HOS 10:13–10:14</a></p>\n<h2>Objects of misplaced trust</h2>\n<h3>Trust in false gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:4\">PSA 40:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:20\">DEU 31:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:2\">PSA 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:17\">ISA 42:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:9-Isa47:10\">ISA 47:9–47:10</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in alliances, real or metaphorical</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:15\">ISA 28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:18\">JER 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in human strength and resources</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:5\">JER 17:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:6-Ps44:7\">PSA 44:6–44:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps146:3\">PSA 146:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:5\">PRO 3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:26\">PRO 28:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:22\">ISA 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:8-Isa22:11\">ISA 22:8–22:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:15-Isa30:16\">ISA 30:15–30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:15\">EZK 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in the outward form of religion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:6-Mic6:8\">MIC 6:6–6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:14\">JER 7:14</a> <em>trust in the temple</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:15\">JER 28:15</a> <em>trust in false prophecy</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:33\">JHN 8:33</a> <em>trust in descent from Abraham</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:17\">ROM 2:17</a> <em>trust in possession of the law</em></p>\n<h3>Trust in one's own righteousness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:19-Rom3:20\">ROM 3:19–3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:13\">EZK 33:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9\">LUK 18:9</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in wealth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17\">1TI 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:24-Job31:25\">JOB 31:24–31:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:5-Ps49:6\">PSA 49:5–49:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:7\">PSA 52:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps62:10\">PSA 62:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:28\">PRO 11:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:7\">JER 48:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:4\">JER 49:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:18-Luke12:20\">LUK 12:18–12:20</a></p>\n<h2>The futility of misplaced trust</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:31\">JOB 15:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:13-Job8:15\">JOB 8:13–8:15</a></p>\n<h3>Futility of trust in false gods</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:37-Deut32:38\">DEU 32:37–32:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:26-1Kgs18:29\">1KI 18:26–18:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:5-Ps115:8\">PSA 115:5–115:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:19\">ISA 37:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18\">HAB 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Futility of trust in human resources</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:6\">ISA 64:6</a> <em>human righteousness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19-Matt6:20\">MAT 6:19–6:20</a> <em>wealth and possessions</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:8\">COL 2:8</a> <em>human philosophy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:13-Jas4:14\">JAS 4:13–4:14</a> <em>human planning</em></p>\n<h3>Futility of trust in others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:19\">PRO 25:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:3\">ISA 31:3</a></p>\n<h2>Failure to trust others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:20\">JDG 11:20</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer12:6\">JER 12:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num21:23\">NUM 21:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:4\">JER 9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:5-Mic7:6\">MIC 7:5–7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:36\">MAT 10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:12\">MRK 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:37-Acts15:38\">ACT 15:37–15:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:14-2Tim4:15\">2TI 4:14–4:15</a></p>",
